article.headline: Sitterud sinks seven 3-pointers in win
article.linkText: Utah's Sitterud rains 3-pointers in upset of TCU
article.story:
SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Lana Sitterud made seven 3s in a
career-high 27-point performance, and Kim Smith added 23 as Utah
beat Texas Christian (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today; No. 23 AP) 85-72 Saturday for its sixth straight
victory.

Clinging to a 67-65 lead, Smith hit two 3s and Sitterud her
seventh of the game to stretch Utah's lead to 76-69. The Utes (7-2)
made nine of 10 from the line in the final 1:33.

Sandora Irvin led the Horned Frogs (7-3) with 20 points and nine
rebounds, and became the school's all-time leading scorer. The
6-foot-3 post player broke the record when she rebounded her own
miss and banked it in with 4:16 left.

Janice Dziuk, who played from 1986-90, held the TCU record of
1,448 points. Irvin, who ended the game with 1,451, already was the
program's career-leading rebounder and shot blocker. Irvin also had
three blocks to move into a tie for ninth place on the NCAA list
with 359.

Shona Thorburn had 12 points and 11 assists for the Utes, whose
only two losses are to top-15 teams at the time they played. Most
of the assists were on penetrations and kick-out passes to Sitterud
and Smith, who went 5-of-5 on 3-point attempts.

TCU dominated inside with a 28-12 point advantage but could not
overcome Utah's long-range accuracy.

Vanessa Clementino had 12 points and JimAnne Baker 11 for TCU,
which has dropped two of its last three games.
